channel.title: MSN or Uploading Wont Work?
channel.description:
Note: The only way I got this picture is I turned GhostSurf back on and it would let me sign into MSN and upload pictures etc...
Ok my problem is that I want to uninstall GhostSurf, Because it is taking up like 155,000 K of memory. So I ended it and my computer runs faster. But I come to a problem when I turn it off I cant log onto MSN, or upload pictures... Anyone got any ideas on how I can remove it and fix my problem? because when i try to remove it, the uninstall box wont get any progress and will stay there at the same area with nothing in it.
Help please I looked through my registry and all to remove this program and I cant even find it in the registry.
[IMG]http://i121.photobucket.com/albums/o218/Bigscape/wtfcompslow.jpg[/img]

item.title: MSN or Uploading Wont Work?
item.dc:creator: @goatee goatee
item.description:
@goatee wrote:

msconfig, diagnostic startup… then see. It happened to me and that’s how I fixed it.

Basically, you need to stop Ghostsurf from starting up, then kill it.
